verbose_text: We then analyzed the correlation between SNHG1 expression and clinicopathological characteristics in AML patients, and found that high SNHG1 expression was significantly related to higher white blood cell (WBC) count, unfavorable cytogenetics, unfavorable European LeukemiaNet (ELN) risk stratification, lower complete remission (CR) rate and higher relapse rate (XREF_TABLE and Table S1).
